Lay v0.3
created lay-reinst | reinstalls Lay from ~/lay
updated install.sh | you can now install lay-reinst
updated install.sh | the ~/lay clone can now sit in /usr/local/lib, so it wont have to be stuck at ~/
updated lay-reinst | lay-reinst reinstalls by removing lay, tks, and tmux, insted of removing the clone
updated lay-uninst | now removes the Lay clone: /usr/local/lib/lay
updated lay.1 | added to manpage
updated lay-reinst | fixed bug
updated lay-uninst | fixed bug
updated lay-uninst | added uninstalling lay-reinst and lay-uninst
updated lay | added window colors and session names

